Press Releases.Title: 31 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
1.      As of 25 August 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 31 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore. Based on our investigations so far, there are no cases in the community.

2.      There is 1 imported case, who had been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore. 

3.      We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.
